{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609049","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609049"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:40:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:40:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16081"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16081","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16081"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.61,0.21,0.14,0.04,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8772"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71578"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8772"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16081"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57074"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"295"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"},{"type":"tags","id":"10625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20953"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20955"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71578","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71578"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EEctopic pregnancy occurs when a fertilised ovum implants outside the uterine cavity, most commonly in the fallopian tube.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a typical feature of symptomatic ectopic pregnancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Lower serum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin levels than expected for gestational age","Higher serum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin levels than intrauterine pregnancy","Absence of vaginal bleeding","Regular menstrual periods","Decreasing abdominal pain over time"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn ectopic pregnancy, \u003Cstrong\u003Eserum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin levels are typically lower than expected\u003C/strong\u003E for gestational age due to suboptimal implantation conditions outside the uterus. This helps distinguish it from a normal intrauterine pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigher serum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin levels\u003C/strong\u003E - Hormone levels are lower in an ectopic pregnancy due to poor trophoblastic development\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbsence of vaginal bleeding\u003C/strong\u003E - Irregular vaginal bleeding is a common presenting symptom\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegular menstrual periods\u003C/strong\u003E - Menstrual irregularity and amenorrhoea are typical after an ectopic pregnancy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreasing abdominal pain\u003C/strong\u003E - Pain typically worsens as the ectopic pregnancy grows\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe classic triad of ectopic pregnancy includes amenorrhoea, vaginal bleeding, and abdominal pain. Early recognition is crucial as rupture can lead to life-threatening haemorrhage.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ectopic pregnancy typically presents with vaginal bleeding, abdominal pain, and lower serum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin levels for the expected gestational age.","Beta-human chorionic gonadotropin levels rise more slowly in ectopic pregnancy due to suboptimal implantation conditions."],"references":["Sivalingam VN, Duncan WC, Kirk E, Shephard LA, Horne AW. Diagnosis and management of ectopic pregnancy. J Fam Plann Reprod Health Care. 2011 Oct;37(4):231-40. doi: 10.1136/jfprhc-2011-0073. Epub 2011 Jul 4. PMID: 21727242; PMCID: PMC3213855.","Mullany K, Minneci M, Monjazeb R, C Coiado O. Overview of ectopic pregnancy diagnosis, management, and innovation. Womens Health (Lond). 2023 Jan-Dec;19:17455057231160349. doi: 10.1177/17455057231160349. PMID: 36999281; PMCID: PMC10071153.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57074"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16081"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57074"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-19T17:10:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T21:02:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8772"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71578"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}}